<br>
So, since Verant won't tell Beastlords what their role in the game is, Beastlords have begun looking at other classes and how they fit in with them.  Since Beastlords rely on their pets as much as Magicians/Necromancers (and maybe even more so), Beastlords started identifying with the other pet classes.  <br>
<br>
However, when Beastlords were first introduced, all pets (Mag, Nec and Bst) were roughly the same strength (excluding the epic pet).  I believe the highest Mag/Nec pets hit for 58 (not sure about epic) and the highest Beastlord pet for 55.  Then, Verant started on caster balancing and Magicians and Necromancers began getting huge upgrade with their pets (true though that a lot of them trickled back to Beastlords and other pet classes).  Mage/Necro pets how can hit 13 points harder than Beastlord pets.  So, Beastlords began to feel left out since they once had fairly equal pets with Magicians and Necromancers and now these two classes were getting stronger pets and Beastlords, once again, were getting nothing.<br>
<br>
It has really come to the point now where Beastlords are so frustrated that it has taken Verant so long to add the simplest things yet other classes are getting big upgrades.  Yes, I know other classes have been waiting for stuff for a long time, but Beastlords really just have a lot of bugs that haven't been worked out yet.<br>
<br>
There aren't that many people that are truely asking for outlandish things.  It's just that there are so many ideas flying around that if you perceive them to be all the demands of the class, it does look rediculous.  There aren't many Beastlords who think we should be as <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm45.showMessage?topicID=216.topic">strong as monks</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> nor are there that many that think we should have the strongest pets in the game.<br>
<br>
Most Beastlords just want the kinks worked out of the class.  We want our class AAs, our spell lines to make more sense, etc.  Sure, there are a lot of ideas flying around about the Beastlord class, but there were also a lot of ideas flying around about the Magician class before it started getting &quot;balanced.&quot;  The fact of the matter is that the Beastlord class is in its infancy and while Verant told other classes what their role would be when the game started, Beastlords are only left to wonder what Verant has in store for us. <p><div align="Center"><img src="http://members.aol.com/nodnarbjh/csig.jpg" alt="Cantatus - Phantasmist and Artisan of the Karana Server" width="253" height="75">
