<br>
Well know what? Ain't gonna happen... You, as Shadowknights, use your pet as a dot - your pet isn't supposed to be tanking for you. Suggestions of aa that would make your pet stronger ( when WE - as THE pet class - do not have such a thing ) are nothing short of laughable. Yes, you don't wear plate as Sks... My ac sucks, my pet should be tanking for me, blah blah.<br>
<br>
If you are unhappy with your class, start something else, and stop trying to take things that have taken us ages to get. Mage has been playing for 3 years, finally gets a good upgrade in power. BST says 'Epic pet r kool, I want something like that too!'. A mage without a pet is NOTHING but a weak wizard surrogate without root, snare, or ports. You have very good utility spells, slows, and can - to a certain extent - tank. Why do you want stronger pets? Did VI say they wanted your class to be all about DPS? Obviously, since they gave you spells with mana and hp regen, then it's NO. Accept it, it deal with it.<br>
<br>
Sure, some discussion over these boards are laughable - I'm afraid some sub-13 years old kids do post here, like on boards all over the net. However, the biggest part of the mage community over these board is constructive, and backs what she says with hard proof. So far, I have only seen BST whining over imaginary slights that should be undone to them. Your pets are different from ours - accept it. Don't compare yourself to our epic - your epic is so ludicrously easy. And it is good, too. People ( like necromancers or beastmasters ) make the mistake of comparing their final pets to our epics, forgetting they have epics that are NOT pets, giving them other edges, and hence should not expect their pets to be as strong as ours. Yes EoT is rare, no it should not be as strong as our epic. It's only a relatively small amount of cash. It can vary from server to server, but it's 10k on Veeshan. Spirit of Khati Sha is a joke to obtain.<br>
<br>
To sum it up - get a grip, and stop whining. Or else, whine when you have reasons to. <p><p><center><img src=http://utenti.tripod.it/Sirya22a/duke></p>

