Just curious, when should we start whining?<br>
<br>
We haven't been given a specific role to fill-or even a non-essential role defined for us, such as DPS.<br>
<br>
We apparently aren't allowed any good weapons-all the good beast-only weapons were given to monks as well, consequently, very few people ever see them.  As it is, I'm 99% certain that there are basically two beastlord only weapons-our epics.  Well, maybe 8, counting newbie claws, I think.  So we are left competing with monks for all our weapons.  Just having beastlord only loot at the high end would make us very happy.<br>
<br>
We have low ac armor-like our monk parents-but without any of the natural ac bonus.  Should we get the entire bonus? No.  But we are a hybrid, we should get part of their advantages.  Those advantages being more than using SOME kunark/velious mid/low level 1hb/2hb, and being on their damage/delay table for fists.<br>
<br>
Every other hybrid has casting bonuses-bst's were left out of that.  Much of this thread states 'You're a hybrid, get over it.  You will be weak.' But we do not get this.<br>
<br>
Beastlords are on the old hybrid casting table-fizzles galore.  Since y'all are so fond of reading our whines, check out the sk vs bst fizzle thread, stickied in the den(general).<br>
<br>
How many patches ago were pets upgraded?  Hasn't the mage pet been upgraded twice, I believe?  Most of the beastlord community would be overjoyed to even get this message from VI/SOE:<br>
&quot;We are aware of the issue regarding beastlord's warder max hits.  That will be looked at during hybrid class balancing, at which point we decide what the hell to do with the unfinished class we released.&quot;<br>
<br>
We'd be happy with the above message, but referring to Class AAs-which we have none of.<br>
<br>
We are an unfinished class-VI/SOE has acknowledged this.  Verant has made virtually no attempt to finish us.  Their only attempt being an upgrade to spiritual purity(very nice!) and a nerf to spiritual strength.<br>
<br>
I would say that the beastlord community is divided about 45/45/10.  45% believing that we should be balanced with OUR melee, and leave pets virtually alone.  45% believing that we should be balanced by bringing our pets power up.  And 10% wishing that VI/SOE(What are they referred to, anyway?) gives us both. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And don't tell me that y'all don't have people like that too, I read this board <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
One thing that I would like to suggest to the mage community-which I enjoy reading, occasionally-is to not make assumptions about the beastlord class.  Maybe Duke of the Sky is just the one person sticking in my mind right now-but I see many assumptions made about beastlords-and 95% of them are wrong.  If you are going to tell us how to balance our class, at least play it a bit first.  I originally planned this as a step by step rebuttal to his post, but I didn't want this to completely come out like a flame.  Instead, I thought that the point of this post-to point out beastlord flaws-would be better served by putting the major ones out in one place.<br>
<br>
