<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Once you realize that you are a hybrid youll be much happier with your class. Some of the people posting on your boards dont seem to realize that and act like they should have the same pet/casting power as a pure casting class.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This doesn't exactly fly. Several reasons.<br>
<br>
One, don't mix &quot;casting&quot; and &quot;pet&quot; power willy nilly.  It's possible for beastlords to have decent &quot;pet&quot; power and crappy &quot;casting&quot; power overall.  Now both are crappy.  Beastlords were advertised as a &quot;pet-dependent melee/hybrid,&quot; which never existed before, so we can't just go assuming that &quot;pets&quot; are only supposed to be halfway decent when used by casters.  Think a little outside the box, just to be fair.  Beastlords paid a hefty price for their pets -- and that is that their melee power got JACKED.<br>
<br>
Two, lots of hybrids match or exceed &quot;pure&quot; classes in some areas.  Rangers exceed warriors in pure *offensive* melee, exceed warriors in archery, exceed druids in tracking, and match druids in snaring.  Other hybrids can say similar things, whereas currently beastlords seem to have everyone from all sides clamoring for them not to do anything well -- and heck, even being a close third with respect to pet damage (and a distant third with respect to pet tanking) is objectionable to some people.  /shrug<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Please dont go invoking the holy name of the epic pet when trying to point out how weak your pets are. Its a lot stronger than a regular pet because of the fact of the epic is absolute torture for mages to get and most will probably never see one in their spellbook.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If you don't go invoking the holy grail of the 50% slow, then we have a deal. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     Seriously, though, 9 out of 10 beastlords agree with you.<br>
